name: __ETextureEncodeEffort
doc:
For encoders that support it (i.e. Oodle), this controls how much time to
spend on finding better encoding.
(These need to match the Oodle OodleTex_EncodeEffortLevel values if you are
using Oodle.)

Default: Let the encoder decide what's best.
Low: Faster encoding, lower quality. Probably don't ship textures encoded at this effort level
High: More time, better quality - good for nightlies / unattended cooks.
